A spokesman for a group of UnitedAirlines employees, who oppose the attempted takeover of Unitedby the Airline Pilots Association, said he met with the newchairman of Allegis, Frank Olson.    William Palmer, the group's spokesman, which claims tospeak for thousands of United employees, said the meeting withOlson was "positive and friendly," but no future meeting dateswere set.    In April the pilots union offered to buy out United, anAllegis subsidiary, through an employee stock ownership plan. Reuter&#3;